            </div>
            <div class="roadmap-item">
                <h3>Phase 3: Network Refinement & Launch Preparation (Tier 3 Funding)</h3>

                <p>Optimize network protocols, finalize dual-network client functionality, and prepare for distributed testing using third tier resources.</p>

        <h4>Network Completion</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Finalize pay-per-store model with TTL.</li>
                    <li>Complete self-custody wallet for storage payments.</li>
                    <li>Finish dual-network client implementation.</li>
                    <li>Build $PUNK creation bridge to $PUNK-DAO tokens.</li>

                </ul>
        <h4>Public Testing</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Deploy public testnet for community validation.</li>
                    <li>Implement testnet faucet for token distribution.</li>
                    <li>Create comprehensive testing guides.</li>
                    <li>Incorporate technical improvement proposals from community review.</li>

                </ul>
        <h4>Security & Compliance</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Conduct comprehensive security audits.</li>
                    <li>Address identified vulnerabilities.</li>
                    <li>Implement monitoring and analytics tools.</li>
                    <li>Finalize cryptographic verification for mainnet deployment.</li>

                </ul>
        <h4>Decentralized Currency Exchange Development</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Implement permissionless currency exchange protocol for $PUNK token with ERC-20 tokens and fiat currency through direct channels secured by node-based multisig verification.</li>
                    <li>Develop secure trade escrow and verification systems.</li>
                    <li>Create trading pairs with selected tokens and fiat currencies.</li>
                    <li>Develop exchange security and anti-manipulation safeguards.</li>

                </ul>
        <div class="code-block">
            <div class="block-header">Phase 3 Details</div>
            <ul>
                <li>Status: Planned  </li>
                <li>Funding: Tier 3 (700,001-1,350,000 USDT) - <span class="highlight highlight-multiplier">4x</span> $PUNK-DAO per USDT</li>
        </div>


            </div>
            <div class="roadmap-item">
                <h3>Phase 4: Network Launch & Ecosystem Development (Tier 4 Funding)</h3>

                <p>Deploy production network infrastructure and extend protocol capabilities using fourth tier resources. the Community Development Fund for long-term ecosystem growth.</p>

        <h4>Network Launch</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Deploy mainnet with complete functionality.</li>
                    <li>Deploy claim contract on Ethereum.</li>
                    <li>Activate bridge service for $PUNK minting.</li>
                    <li>Implement multiplier mechanism for original token holders.</li>
                    <li>Implement soulbound token mechanism.</li>
                    <li>Establish initial node operator network.</li>

                </ul>
        <h4>Launch Campaign</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Announce network launch and claim process.</li>
                    <li>Launch social media presence (Twitter, Mastodon, Telegram).</li>
                    <li>Distribute technical documentation to potential storage users and node operators.</li>
                    <li>Document technical implementation of cypherpunk principles and censorship resistance.</li>

                </ul>
        <h4>Application Layer Development</h4>

                <ul>
                    <li>Expand decentralized currency exchange trading pair options.</li>
                    <li>Establish network-wide indexing and search functionality (collaborative between nodes and clients).</li>
                    <li>Implement basic client-side social media functionality.</li>
                    <li>Develop decentralized trading platform for goods and services (separate from currency exchange).</li>
                    <li>Implement anonymous usage capability (network hops).</li>

                </ul>
        <div class="code-block">
            <div class="block-header">Phase 4 Details</div>
            <ul>
                <li>Status: Planned  </li>
                <li>Funding: Tier 4 (1,350,001-2,350,000+ USDT) - <span class="highlight highlight-multiplier">2x</span> $PUNK-DAO per USDT  </li>
                <li>Includes allocation of unsold tokens <strong>60/40</strong> to Founder/Developer Pool and Community Development Fund</li>
        </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</content>
<content>
    <!-- Frequently Asked Questions Section -->
    <section id="faq" class="content-section">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-category">
            <input type="checkbox" id="category-general-information" class="category-toggle">
            <label for="category-general-information" class="faq-category-header">
                <h3>General Information</h3>
                <span class="category-arrow">▼</span>
            </label>
            <div class="faq-category-content">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q1" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q1" class="faq-question">
                        What is StorPunk?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>StorPunk is a decentralized ecosystem implementing core cypherpunk principles through cryptographic privacy, individual sovereignty, and resistance to centralized control. While built on a foundation of configurable data storage, the network aims to provide a comprehensive suite of tools for digital sovereignty including financial infrastructure, trading platforms, and communication tools.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q2" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q2" class="faq-question">
                        How does StorPunk differ from Autonomi Network?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>StorPunk forks the Autonomi Network codebase but introduces significant changes, including:</p>
                        <ul><li><strong>Temporary Data Model:</strong> Unlike Autonomi's permanent data storage, StorPunk focuses on temporary data storage with configurable retention periods.</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Native Token:</strong> StorPunk has its own native token ($PUNK) for network operations, separate from the $PUNK-DAO governance token.</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Dual-Network Client:</strong> The client supports both StorPunk and Autonomi networks for comprehensive data management without requiring multiple applications.</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q3" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q3" class="faq-question">
                        Why did StorPunk choose temporary data storage?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The implementation of temporary data storage provides several key benefits:</p>
                        <p>1. <strong>Economic Sustainability:</strong> Prevents network bloat and ensures users always pay market rates for storage</p>
                        <p>2. <strong>Operational Resilience:</strong> Eliminates the risk of cascade collapse from unfunded data maintenance obligations</p>
                        <p>3. <strong>Market-Based Pricing:</strong> Clients pay for exactly what they need, for exactly how long they need it</p>
                        <p>4. <strong>User Control:</strong> Individuals determine data retention periods rather than relying on permanent storage defaults</p>
                        <p>Privacy is achieved through cryptographic protection, not through data expiration mechanisms.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q4" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q4" class="faq-question">
                        What are the network features?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Launch Features:</strong></p>
                        <ul><li><strong>Configurable Data Storage Network:</strong> Temporary data retention with dual-network client supporting both StorPunk and Autonomi</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Native Network Token ($PUNK):</strong> Fixed-supply token for all network operations</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Decentralized Currency Exchange:</strong> Direct trading between $PUNK tokens, fiat currencies, and selected cryptocurrencies</li></ul>
                        <p><strong>Post-Launch Features:</strong></p>
                        <ul><li><strong>Network Search:</strong> Indexing and search functionality for public data</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Social Media Communications:</strong> Client-side social media functionality</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Decentralized Trading Platform:</strong> General trading platform for goods and services</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Network Hops:</strong> Anonymous usage capabilities similar to Tor</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q5" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q5" class="faq-question">
                        How does the dual-network client work?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The dual-network client allows users to:</p>
                        <ul><li>Store data to both StorPunk and Autonomi networks from a single interface</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Use StorPunk for temporary storage needs</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Use Autonomi for permanent storage requirements</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Manage both network tokens ($PUNK and ANT) in one application</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Access the strengths of each network without switching applications</li></ul>
                        <p>Note: Using Autonomi features requires owning ANT tokens in addition to $PUNK tokens.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-category">
            <input type="checkbox" id="category-dao-and-governance" class="category-toggle">
            <label for="category-dao-and-governance" class="faq-category-header">
                <h3>DAO and Governance</h3>
                <span class="category-arrow">▼</span>
            </label>
            <div class="faq-category-content">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q6" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q6" class="faq-question">
                        What is the $PUNK-DAO token?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>$PUNK-DAO is an ERC-20 token that serves two purposes:</p>
                        <p>1. <strong>Fundraising:</strong> Sold in tiers to raise capital for sustainable, long-term development.</p>
                        <p>2. <strong>Permanent Governance:</strong> Token holders vote on key decisions via Snapshot.org, maintaining their voice throughout the project's lifetime.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q7" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q7" class="faq-question">
                        How does the tiered sale work?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>$PUNK-DAO tokens are sold at a <strong>1:1</strong> ratio with USDT across all tiers. The tier determines your $PUNK network token multiplier at launch:</p>
                        <ul><li>Tier 1: 1 USDT = 1 $PUNK-DAO with <strong>16x</strong> multiplier at launch (0-250,000 USDT)</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Tier 2: 1 USDT = 1 $PUNK-DAO with <strong>8x</strong> multiplier at launch (250,001-700,000 USDT)</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Tier 3: 1 USDT = 1 $PUNK-DAO with <strong>4x</strong> multiplier at launch (700,001-1,350,000 USDT)</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Tier 4: 1 USDT = 1 $PUNK-DAO with <strong>2x</strong> multiplier at launch (1,350,001-2,350,000+ USDT)</li></ul>
                        <p>Each tier has a limited supply. Tiers are initiated only when needed (typically when runway decreases to 6 months). Unsold tokens from each tier are allocated <strong>60/40</strong> between the Founder/Core Developer Pool and the Community Development Fund.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q8" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q8" class="faq-question">
                        What is the hold-to-double reward?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The token claim mechanism provides an <strong>additional 2x multiplier</strong> for original purchasers who maintained their position without transfer. For example, a Tier 1 buyer with a <strong>16x</strong> multiplier receives a <strong>32x</strong> multiplier (<strong>16x</strong> × <strong>2x</strong>) if they never transferred their tokens. Secondary buyers receive only the base tier multiplier. This structure incentivizes long-term participation in governance and development.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q9" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q9" class="faq-question">
                        What happens to my $PUNK-DAO tokens after claiming $PUNK?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>After claiming native tokens, $PUNK-DAO tokens become <strong>soulbound</strong> (cryptographically locked to your wallet). This mechanism:</p>
                        <ul><li>You cannot transfer or sell them</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>You keep full voting rights forever</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Your governance voice is permanent</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Market confusion is prevented (only unused tokens trade)</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q10" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q10" class="faq-question">
                        How do I vote on proposals?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Voting happens on Snapshot.org (gasless and free):</p>
                        <p>1. Visit snapshot.org/#/storpunk</p>
                        <p>2. Connect your wallet (MetaMask, etc.)</p>
                        <p>3. Browse active proposals</p>
                        <p>4. Click "Vote" and select your choice</p>
                        <p>5. Sign a message (no gas fees!)</p>
                        <p>Your voting power equals your $PUNK-DAO token balance, whether the tokens are used or unused.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q11" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q11" class="faq-question">
                        What is the Community Development Fund?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The Community Development Fund is a long-term initiative that receives <strong>40%</strong> of all unsold tokens:</p>
                        <ul><li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Funds ecosystem development, community projects, and ongoing maintenance after the main development phases are complete</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Community developers must hold at least <strong>100</strong> $PUNK-DAO tokens to receive grants from the fund</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Governance:</strong> Fund allocations are decided by DAO voting through Snapshot.org</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Sustainability:</strong> Designed to support the project ecosystem for years or decades after the initial development phases</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-category">
            <input type="checkbox" id="category-network-and-technical" class="category-toggle">
            <label for="category-network-and-technical" class="faq-category-header">
                <h3>Network and Technical</h3>
                <span class="category-arrow">▼</span>
            </label>
            <div class="faq-category-content">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q12" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q12" class="faq-question">
                        How do I claim my $PUNK tokens?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Important:</strong> The claim contract is separate from the DAO contract and is only deployed when the StorPunk network launches (Phase 4). During pre-launch phases (0-3), $PUNK-DAO tokens remain fully transferable on Ethereum.</p>
                        <p><strong>Claim Process (Available only after StorPunk network launch):</strong></p>
                        <p>1. StorPunk network launches and a separate claim contract is deployed on Ethereum</p>
                        <p>2. User calls the claim function on this new claim contract, providing their StorPunk network address</p>
                        <p>3. The claim contract verifies your $PUNK-DAO token balance and transaction history</p>
                        <p>4. Your $PUNK-DAO tokens immediately become <strong>soulbound</strong> (permanently non-transferable) via cross-contract integration</p>
                        <p>5. A bridge service detects the claim event and mints your $PUNK tokens on StorPunk at the appropriate multiplier</p>
                        <p><strong>How Soulbound Works:</strong> The claim contract marks your address as having claimed, and the DAO contract's transfer function checks this status before allowing any transfers. This creates an on-chain enforcement mechanism that permanently prevents transfers while preserving governance rights.</p>
                        <p><strong>Warning:</strong> Once you claim, your $PUNK-DAO tokens become permanently non-transferable, though they retain full governance rights. Only claim when you're ready to use the StorPunk network.</p>
                        <p>The system verifies original ownership through transaction history and applies appropriate multipliers: <strong>double</strong> for original holders, <strong>base rate</strong> for secondary purchasers.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q13" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q13" class="faq-question">
                        Can I use StorPunk with Autonomi Network?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes. The dual-network client architecture supports both systems:</p>
                        <ul><li>Upload and download from either network</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Use the appropriate currency for each network</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Leverage each network's unique strengths</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>StorPunk: Temporary, efficient storage</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Autonomi: Permanent, immutable storage</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q14" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q14" class="faq-question">
                        What is the decentralized currency exchange?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Available at launch, the decentralized currency exchange operates directly on the StorPunk network. It enables direct trading between $PUNK tokens, fiat currencies, and selected cryptocurrencies without intermediaries or central points of failure.</p>
                        <p>The exchange maintains security through network architecture while protecting participant privacy.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q15" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q15" class="faq-question">
                        What is the decentralized trading platform?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Developed post-launch, this platform will support unrestricted exchange of goods and services through a fully decentralized marketplace on the StorPunk network. This creates censorship-resistant alternatives to traditional marketplaces with direct transactions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q16" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q16" class="faq-question">
                        How does network privacy work?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The system implements network privacy protections including anonymous usage capability through network hops. These features protect user identity and location while maintaining communication and transaction capabilities across the network.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q17" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q17" class="faq-question">
                        What programming language is StorPunk built with?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>StorPunk is built primarily using Rust, following the same technology stack as Autonomi Network since StorPunk is a fork of that codebase.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q18" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q18" class="faq-question">
                        Will I be notified before my data expires?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, as a post-launch client feature, the StorPunk client will track data expiration dates and notify users before their data expires. The client will also support automated renewal capabilities for stored data, allowing users to extend storage periods without manual intervention.</p>
                        <p><strong>Auto-renewal Requirements:</strong> Automated renewal only works when your computer is on, the StorPunk client is running, and the client has access to your wallet keys to enable automatic payments for storage extensions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-category">
            <input type="checkbox" id="category-development-and-timeline" class="category-toggle">
            <label for="category-development-and-timeline" class="faq-category-header">
                <h3>Development and Timeline</h3>
                <span class="category-arrow">▼</span>
            </label>
            <div class="faq-category-content">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q19" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q19" class="faq-question">
                        What is the development timeline?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>StorPunk follows a <strong>4-phase</strong> development approach:</p>
                        <ul><li><strong>Phase 0:</strong> Foundation Building (Pre-Funding) - Website, DAO structure, initial operations</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Phase 1:</strong> Core Team Assembly & Initial Development (Tier 1 Funding)</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Phase 2:</strong> Full Team & Core Development (Tier 2 Funding)</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Phase 3:</strong> Network Refinement & Launch Preparation (Tier 3 Funding) - Including decentralized currency exchange development</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>Phase 4:</strong> Network Launch & Ecosystem Development (Tier 4 Funding)</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="q20" class="question-toggle">
                    <label for="q20" class="faq-question">
                        Why a phase-based funding plan?
                        <span class="question-arrow">▼</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Our <strong>4-phase</strong> development plan with aligned funding ensures:</p>
                        <ul><li>Development continues regardless of market conditions</li></ul>
                        <ul><li><strong>100%</strong> remote contractor team for global talent and efficiency</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Just-in-time funding reduces dilution</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Each tier directly funds a specific development phase</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>Community has clear visibility into progress</li></ul>
                        <ul><li>DAO governance continues long after main development through the Community Development Fund</li></ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
