    <!-- StorPunk DAO Constitution Section -->
    <section id="constitution" class="content-section">
        <h2>StorPunk DAO Constitution</h2>

        <h3>Preamble</h3>

        <p>We, the members of the StorPunk Decentralized Autonomous Organization, unite under the principles of the Cypherpunk Manifesto to build and govern a system that empowers individual privacy, freedom, and sovereignty in the digital age.</p>

        <p>Privacy is necessary for an open society. We build StorPunk to provide temporary, encrypted storage that leaves no permanent trace—a tool for those who value their right to selectively reveal information. Through cryptography and decentralized governance, we defend privacy not through words but through code.</p>

        <p>This Constitution defines the governance framework while preserving the immutable core mission of StorPunk: creating a temporary storage network that implements cypherpunk principles of privacy, cryptographic protection, and individual sovereignty.</p>

        <h3>Key Constitutional Principles</h3>

        <p>- <strong>Privacy First</strong>: Default to anonymous, encrypted operations</p>
        <p>- <strong>Individual Sovereignty</strong>: Empower users to control their data</p>
        <p>- <strong>Decentralization</strong>: Resist centralized control or censorship</p>
        <p>- <strong>Transparency</strong>: Open source code and verifiable operations</p>
        <p>- <strong>Immutable Mission</strong>: Temporary storage with automatic expiration</p>

        <h3>Governance Structure</h3>

        <p>The StorPunk DAO operates through:</p>

        <p>- <strong>Token-Based Voting</strong>: $PUNK-DAO holders vote on all governance proposals</p>
        <p>- <strong>Snapshot Governance</strong>: Gasless voting through snapshot.org</p>
        <p>- <strong>Soulbound Rights</strong>: Permanent voting rights even after claiming native tokens</p>
        <p>- <strong>Community Fund</strong>: 40% of unsold tokens allocated for ongoing development</p>
        <p>- <strong>Decentralized Decision Making</strong>: No central authority controls the network</p>

        <h3>Constitutional Protections</h3>

        <p>- <strong>Immutable Core Mission</strong>: The temporary storage focus cannot be changed</p>
        <p>- <strong>Privacy Guarantees</strong>: User data remains encrypted and anonymous</p>
        <p>- <strong>Censorship Resistance</strong>: No entity can block access to the network</p>
        <p>- <strong>Open Source</strong>: All code must remain publicly verifiable</p>
        <p>- <strong>Community Control</strong>: Token holders retain ultimate authority</p>

        <div class="download-block">
            <a href="storpunk-dao-constitution.pdf" class="download-link" target="_blank">StorPunk DAO Constitution (PDF)</a>
        </div>

        <ul>
            <li>Contains complete governance framework</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Details all token holder rights and responsibilities</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Outlines amendment procedures and dispute resolution</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>Establishes perpetual DAO governance through the Community Development Fund</li>
        </ul>

    </section>
</content>
